reviews.text: Nice long platforms which is great for your own individual personal space..... Genuinely always a member of staff floating about ... Regular connections to Waterloo ... But the stairs ... Yea take it this way the station is highly elevated..

The lift has been broken for about a month now and when I asked for help with the buggy they said, there was nobody there to help and that in future I needed to go to Clapham Junction - a 40min wall away. A lovely lady helped me as she saw me struggle up three flights of stairs with my one year old. Very disappointed and upset by the lack of empathy and help offered. Public transport should be for everyone - people with buggies are limited enough as big all stations have lifts. I feel that stations with lifts should do everyone they can to keep them working - and surely a month is ample time to get a lift fixed!
